description:
We’re growing and looking for a **Product Designer** to join our Payments team. Join the team behind one of the world’s fastest-growing gaming marketplaces.

**About** **Eldorado.gg**

* Launched in 2019, headquartered in **Vilnius, Simbiocity** (formerly Technopolis);
* A leading digital marketplace for **in-game items, accounts, and services**;
* Supporting **150+ popular games** including **GTA5, Roblox, FC25, RuneScape, World of Warcraft**, **League of Legends, Fortnite**, and more;
* Trusted by gamers worldwide with **over 7 million monthly visits**;
* Built for **security, speed, and simplicity** in digital trading;
* A team of **100+ people** focused on delivering an exceptional experience for our users.



**BREAKDOWN:**

* Lead the end-to-end design process with a focus on UX for checkout, guest checkout, shopping cart;
* Design clear, intuitive, and trustworthy experiences across core purchase flows for both buyers and sellers;
* Map and visualize user flows for checkout and related journeys to align the team on the customer experience;
* Work closely with PMs, engineers, and data analysts to shape product direction and make user-centered decisions;
* Use qualitative insights, quantitative data, and A/B testing to validate, refine, and improve your designs;
* Continuously look for ways to improve the experience for buyers and sellers, especially in areas tied to conversion and safety;
* Give and receive thoughtful feedback to help raise the quality bar across the design team.

**SKILLS YOU’LL NEED**

* 3+ years of experience designing digital products, ideally in fast-paced B2C or marketplace environments;
* Demonstrated ability to own end-to-end product design, from discovery and strategy to execution and delivery;
* Strong UI and interaction design skills, supported by a user-focused, data-informed portfolio. Be sure to **include a portfolio link in your CV**;
* Proficient in Figma and experienced with design systems;
* Experience with user-centered design and conducting research independently;
* Clear and confident in communicating design decisions to stakeholders;
* Strong ownership mentality with a proactive attitude, comfortable identifying design opportunities;
* Hands-on experience with A/B testing is a strong plus.

**WHAT WE OFFER**

* Hybrid work model: work 4 days at our Vilnius office (Simbiocity), and 1 remote.
* Office perks: free parking by the office, a fully stocked kitchen, Friday bun breakfasts, and a gaming room (table football, driving simulator, PS5, Xbox One). Pets are always welcome, and we love a good get-together - from game nights to sports events.
* Development: internal library, latest tools and technology, professional conferences, and mentorship to level up your skills, opportunities for internal career growth.
* Health and fitness: Private health insurance (after trial), join your colleagues for fun, no-cost volleyball games at Delfi Arena, sick days (no doctor’s note needed).
* Extras you’ll love: Monthly top-ups for your Eldorado.gg account (after trial), gifts for graduations, weddings and new parents, partner discounts, and referral bonuses.

 **GROSS SALARY**

* The salary range for this position is **€3000 – €5500 gross** per month, depending on your experience.


Think you’re the right fit? Let’s create something epic together.
